          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Samples for charged particle irradiations were high",
                "purity (>99.99%) nat-SrCo3, nat-CeO2, Pr2O3, nat-Nd2O3",
                "and Tm2O3 powder prepared by sedimentation technique.",
                "The fine powder was suspended in water-free acetone",
                "and in some cases 3 to 5% cellulose nitrate.",
                "200 microliter suspension was used for each sample.",
                "Target backing was 25 um thick Cu foil 13 mm in",
                "diameter. The resulting target layer was 10 mm in",
                "diameter. The deposited layer was covered by 10 um",
                "of Al foil.",
                "Preparing the nat-RbCl target the powder was pressed",
                "on an Al foil of 10 um thickness under a pressure of",
                "6 ton/cm2 for 15 min then was covered by 10 um thick",
                "Al foil.",
                "For neutron irradiations the samples were 1.5 to 2.5 g",
                "of nat-Eu2O3 mixed with 2.5 g KCl and pressed at",
                "10 ton/cm2 to a pallet of 2 cm diameter and 0.3 mm",
                "thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Stack target technique",
                "proton energies:12, 16, 20 MeV",
                "He-3 energies: 25, 36 MeV",
                "He-4 energy:26.5 MeV",
                "Stacks containing Ti and Cu monitor foils were",
                "irradiated with beam of 100 nA. The charge was measured",
                "a Faraday-cup type target holder.",
                "The energy degradation was calculated by using formula",
                "of Wiliamson et al. CEA-R 3042(1966).",
                "Samples and monitor foils were measured",
                "non-destructively."
              ]
            }
          ],
